  "response": "Charles Lee and Robert E. Lee were not closely related, though they shared the same last name and both played notable roles in American history.\n\n**Charles Lee** (1732\u20131782) was a British-born military officer who served as a general in the Continental Army during the American Revolutionary War. He was controversial for his often erratic behavior and was eventually court-martialed for his conduct during the Battle of Monmouth.\n\n**Robert E. Lee** (1807\u20131870) was a Confederate general during the American Civil War. He is best known for leading the Army of Northern Virginia and is often remembered as a central figure in the Confederacy.\n\nWhile both men were involved in significant conflicts in American history, there is no evidence of a direct familial connection between them. Their shared surname is coincidental rather than indicative of a close family relationship.",
